<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="226" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,314,1779]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,530,555]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The most distinctively coloured species of this genus (
<figureCitation box="[941,1030,530,555]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 − 28" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1919,1941]" captionTargetBox="[215,1369,194,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[215,1369,194,1892]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 17 − 28. Sclerotia gen. nov. spp. males. 17, 18 Scl. aquatilis. 19, 20 Luciola cingulata type male (MCSN). 21, 22 Luciola brahmina type male (MNHN). 23, 24 Luciola seriata holotype male (MCSN). 25, 26 Scl. carinata male (SAMA). 27, 28 Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype males (NHMHAU). 17, 19, 21, 23, 25, 27, 28 dorsal; 18, 20, 22, 24, 26 ventral. Specimens are not to scale and are assembled to allow comparison of elytral and abdominal features." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258001/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Figs 25</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1041,1116,530,555]" captionStart="FIGURES 74 − 85" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1841,1863]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,195,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,195,1819]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 74 − 85. Scl. carinata males and female (76). 74, 76 dorsal (76 anterior half of body only); 77 aedeagal sheath ventral; 78 − 80 tergite 8 with sclerites (78, 80 dorsal, 79 ventral; posterior left margin of 79, 80 incomplete); 81, 82 abdomen ventral (81) and right lateral (82); 83 − 85 aedeagus 83 ventral; 84 dorsal; 85 left lateral. Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 74, 75; 78 − 80; 83, 85." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258009/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">74, 75</figureCitation>
); pronotum yellow with two median dark spots, elytra brown with pale yellow lateral margin, apex, suture and four pale interstitial lines; median anterior margin of sheath tergite with shallow margination; right side of posterior margin of sheath sternite with a short angulate projection which represents the end of the oblique ridge of the sheath sternite, otherwise posterior margin truncate with left corner rounded (
<figureCitation box="[727,811,674,699]" captionStart="FIGURES 74 − 85" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1841,1863]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,195,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,195,1819]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 74 − 85. Scl. carinata males and female (76). 74, 76 dorsal (76 anterior half of body only); 77 aedeagal sheath ventral; 78 − 80 tergite 8 with sclerites (78, 80 dorsal, 79 ventral; posterior left margin of 79, 80 incomplete); 81, 82 abdomen ventral (81) and right lateral (82); 83 − 85 aedeagus 83 ventral; 84 dorsal; 85 left lateral. Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 74, 75; 78 − 80; 83, 85." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258009/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 77</figureCitation>
). Females macropterous, larvae unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="226" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,314,1779]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,429,710,735]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Male redescription</emphasis>
. 
<quantity box="[446,614,711,735]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.03" metricValueMax="1.04" metricValueMin="1.02" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" unit="mm" value="10.3" valueMax="10.4" valueMin="10.2">10.2–10.4 mm</quantity>
long; 2.4 X as long as wide. Colour (
<figureCitation box="[1070,1207,710,735]" captionStart="FIGURES 17 − 28" captionStartId="15.[151,264,1919,1941]" captionTargetBox="[215,1369,194,1888]" captionTargetId="figure@15.[215,1369,194,1892]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURES 17 − 28. Sclerotia gen. nov. spp. males. 17, 18 Scl. aquatilis. 19, 20 Luciola cingulata type male (MCSN). 21, 22 Luciola brahmina type male (MNHN). 23, 24 Luciola seriata holotype male (MCSN). 25, 26 Scl. carinata male (SAMA). 27, 28 Scl. fui sp. nov. paratype males (NHMHAU). 17, 19, 21, 23, 25, 27, 28 dorsal; 18, 20, 22, 24, 26 ventral. Specimens are not to scale and are assembled to allow comparison of elytral and abdominal features." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258001/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Figs 25, 26</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1223,1301,710,735]" captionStart="FIGURES 74 − 85" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1841,1863]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,195,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,195,1819]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 74 − 85. Scl. carinata males and female (76). 74, 76 dorsal (76 anterior half of body only); 77 aedeagal sheath ventral; 78 − 80 tergite 8 with sclerites (78, 80 dorsal, 79 ventral; posterior left margin of 79, 80 incomplete); 81, 82 abdomen ventral (81) and right lateral (82); 83 − 85 aedeagus 83 ventral; 84 dorsal; 85 left lateral. Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 74, 75; 78 − 80; 83, 85." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258009/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">74, 75</figureCitation>
): Pronotum orange yellow with two median dark markings; MS and MN yellow; elytra brown with pale yellow lateral margin, pale apex, suture and four pale interstitial lines; fine thin pale lines occur between suture and interstitial line 1, between lines 1 and 2, and between 3 and 4; head between eyes, labrum and scape yellow; remainder of antennae brown; palpi light brown; ventral aspect of thorax dingy yellow, all legs yellow with dark brown tarsi; abdominal 
<date box="[151,213,891,915]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">V2–4</date>
brighter yellow due in part to semi-transparency of cuticle and underlying fat body; 
<date box="[1156,1191,890,915]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">V5</date>
yellow with posterior 1/3 dark brown; light organs in 
<date box="[505,541,926,951]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">V6</date>
, 7 creamy yellow; dorsal abdomen yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,314,1779]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
Pronotum: width subequal humeral width; W/L 1.6–1.8; L/BL 0.18–0.19; W/GHW 1.3; median posterior margin broadly and shallowly emarginated. Elytron: 0.80–0.82 as long as total body length. Head: SIW/GHW 0.15. 
<typeStatus box="[151,207,1035,1059]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Type</typeStatus>
has apical right palpomere with 4 teeth, basal tooth broad; other males have 3 teeth on right apical palpomere; apical left palpomere with 5 teeth in 
<typeStatus box="[576,627,1071,1095]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">type</typeStatus>
, other males have 2 (basal tooth broad). Antennae slightly longer than GHW. Abdomen: 
<date box="[354,388,1107,1130]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">V7</date>
with wide shallow anterior emargination.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,314,1779]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
Aedeagal sheath sclerites (
<figureCitation box="[510,648,1142,1167]" captionStart="FIGURES 74 − 85" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1841,1863]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,195,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,195,1819]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 74 − 85. Scl. carinata males and female (76). 74, 76 dorsal (76 anterior half of body only); 77 aedeagal sheath ventral; 78 − 80 tergite 8 with sclerites (78, 80 dorsal, 79 ventral; posterior left margin of 79, 80 incomplete); 81, 82 abdomen ventral (81) and right lateral (82); 83 − 85 aedeagus 83 ventral; 84 dorsal; 85 left lateral. Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 74, 75; 78 − 80; 83, 85." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258009/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Figs 78−80</figureCitation>
): ventral sclerite approximately triangular in outline with narrowed proximal end, sides not thickened and elongate raised area just to left of centre (
<figureCitation box="[1131,1264,1178,1203]" captionStart="FIGURES 74 − 85" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1841,1863]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,195,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,195,1819]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 74 − 85. Scl. carinata males and female (76). 74, 76 dorsal (76 anterior half of body only); 77 aedeagal sheath ventral; 78 − 80 tergite 8 with sclerites (78, 80 dorsal, 79 ventral; posterior left margin of 79, 80 incomplete); 81, 82 abdomen ventral (81) and right lateral (82); 83 − 85 aedeagus 83 ventral; 84 dorsal; 85 left lateral. Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 74, 75; 78 − 80; 83, 85." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258009/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Figs.78−80</figureCitation>
); right sclerite appearing Y shaped, with three projections to the right, two symmetrical, apically rounded with deep emargination separating them (the arms of the “Y”), and third projection a short hook on right side at the base of the emargination (
<figureCitation box="[313,397,1286,1311]" captionStart="FIGURES 74 − 85" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1841,1863]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,195,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,195,1819]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 74 − 85. Scl. carinata males and female (76). 74, 76 dorsal (76 anterior half of body only); 77 aedeagal sheath ventral; 78 − 80 tergite 8 with sclerites (78, 80 dorsal, 79 ventral; posterior left margin of 79, 80 incomplete); 81, 82 abdomen ventral (81) and right lateral (82); 83 − 85 aedeagus 83 ventral; 84 dorsal; 85 left lateral. Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 74, 75; 78 − 80; 83, 85." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258009/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 79</figureCitation>
); left sclerite roughly triangular in outline, with thickened central ridges, and slender apically rounded anterior projection arising from the anterior ventral surface (
<figureCitation box="[924,1055,1322,1347]" captionStart="FIGURES 74 − 85" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1841,1863]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,195,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,195,1819]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 74 − 85. Scl. carinata males and female (76). 74, 76 dorsal (76 anterior half of body only); 77 aedeagal sheath ventral; 78 − 80 tergite 8 with sclerites (78, 80 dorsal, 79 ventral; posterior left margin of 79, 80 incomplete); 81, 82 abdomen ventral (81) and right lateral (82); 83 − 85 aedeagus 83 ventral; 84 dorsal; 85 left lateral. Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 74, 75; 78 − 80; 83, 85." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258009/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Figs 79, 80</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,314,1779]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
Aedeagal sheath (
<figureCitation box="[400,485,1358,1383]" captionStart="FIGURES 74 − 85" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1841,1863]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,195,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,195,1819]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 74 − 85. Scl. carinata males and female (76). 74, 76 dorsal (76 anterior half of body only); 77 aedeagal sheath ventral; 78 − 80 tergite 8 with sclerites (78, 80 dorsal, 79 ventral; posterior left margin of 79, 80 incomplete); 81, 82 abdomen ventral (81) and right lateral (82); 83 − 85 aedeagus 83 ventral; 84 dorsal; 85 left lateral. Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 74, 75; 78 − 80; 83, 85." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258009/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 77</figureCitation>
): with oblique median ridge projecting into a short posterolateral projection on right side which curves slightly dorsally; rest of posterior margin of sheath sternite truncate; median anterior margin of sheath tergite shallowly emarginated (not clearly visible in 
<figureCitation box="[814,897,1430,1455]" captionStart="FIGURES 74 − 85" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1841,1863]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,195,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,195,1819]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 74 − 85. Scl. carinata males and female (76). 74, 76 dorsal (76 anterior half of body only); 77 aedeagal sheath ventral; 78 − 80 tergite 8 with sclerites (78, 80 dorsal, 79 ventral; posterior left margin of 79, 80 incomplete); 81, 82 abdomen ventral (81) and right lateral (82); 83 − 85 aedeagus 83 ventral; 84 dorsal; 85 left lateral. Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 74, 75; 78 − 80; 83, 85." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258009/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 77</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,314,1779]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[325,459,1466,1491]" captionStart="FIGURES 74 − 85" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1841,1863]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,195,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,195,1819]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 74 − 85. Scl. carinata males and female (76). 74, 76 dorsal (76 anterior half of body only); 77 aedeagal sheath ventral; 78 − 80 tergite 8 with sclerites (78, 80 dorsal, 79 ventral; posterior left margin of 79, 80 incomplete); 81, 82 abdomen ventral (81) and right lateral (82); 83 − 85 aedeagus 83 ventral; 84 dorsal; 85 left lateral. Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 74, 75; 78 − 80; 83, 85." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258009/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Figs 83−85</figureCitation>
): L/W of type 1.75, of NHML specimens 2.5; LL subequal in length; posterior margin of LL slightly sinuate with longer inner margin; inner margins not hooked; LL diverge along their dorsal length. Length basal piece/total length aedeagus 0.5 (
<quantity box="[662,727,1538,1563]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.524" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" unit="in" value="0.6">0.6 in</quantity>
type)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,314,1779]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,1574,1599]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Female</emphasis>
: Colour (
<figureCitation box="[402,492,1574,1599]" captionStart="FIGURES 74 − 85" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1841,1863]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,195,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,195,1819]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 74 − 85. Scl. carinata males and female (76). 74, 76 dorsal (76 anterior half of body only); 77 aedeagal sheath ventral; 78 − 80 tergite 8 with sclerites (78, 80 dorsal, 79 ventral; posterior left margin of 79, 80 incomplete); 81, 82 abdomen ventral (81) and right lateral (82); 83 − 85 aedeagus 83 ventral; 84 dorsal; 85 left lateral. Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 74, 75; 78 − 80; 83, 85." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258009/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 76</figureCitation>
): as for male, except for basal abdominal ventrites which are yellow with black posterior half of 
<date box="[338,376,1610,1635]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">V5</date>
; 
<date box="[387,424,1611,1634]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">V7</date>
, 8 orange yellow. Posterior margin of 
<date box="[852,886,1611,1634]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">V7</date>
broadly and shallowly emarginated.
</paragraph>
