<subSubSection pageId="25" pageNumber="226" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1437,314,1779]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1646,1671]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Olivier" box="[324,486,1646,1671]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226" refString="Olivier, E. (1885) Catalogue des Lampyrides faisant partie des collections du Musee Civique de Genes. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova, (2 a) 2, 333 - 374." type="journal article" year="1885">Olivier (1885)</bibRefCitation>
described an ‘immature’ male from 
<collectingRegion box="[907,1000,1647,1671]" country="Indonesia" name="Sumatera Utara" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Sumatra</collectingRegion>
(perhaps meaning it was smaller than the typical specimens) with tibiae black on their outer side and a reversible hood formed by T8 over 
<date box="[1346,1380,1683,1706]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">V7</date>
(LB translation and interpretation of the original French). In 
<taxonomicName box="[782,882,1718,1743]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Sclerotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="25" pageNumber="247" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[782,882,1718,1743]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Sclerotia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. the thin margins of tergite 8 partially enfold the sides and sometimes the apex of ventrite 7 (this may be a partially post-mortem effect; see 
<figureCitation box="[1210,1339,1754,1779]" captionStart="FIGURES 74 − 85" captionStartId="27.[151,264,1841,1863]" captionTargetBox="[151,1434,195,1780]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,195,1819]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 74 − 85. Scl. carinata males and female (76). 74, 76 dorsal (76 anterior half of body only); 77 aedeagal sheath ventral; 78 − 80 tergite 8 with sclerites (78, 80 dorsal, 79 ventral; posterior left margin of 79, 80 incomplete); 81, 82 abdomen ventral (81) and right lateral (82); 83 − 85 aedeagus 83 ventral; 84 dorsal; 85 left lateral. Scale lines are 1 mm. These figures share scale lines: 74, 75; 78 − 80; 83, 85." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/258009/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Figs 81, 82</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
